title: Field of Armor for Man Keychain
description:
Keychain developed from South German, Nuremberg, Field Armor for Man, c. 1520, from The Art Institute of Chicago’s collection.

Skillfully forged of steel, this composite armor achieves its beauty with the simple elegance of its austere lines and form rather than its surface decoration. 

A great gift for yourself of a friend.

  • Dimensions of charm: 2.5 x 1.5 in.
  • Materials: Brass with colored enamel.
